    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at some new high-protein kibble for my Lab. He's getting up there in age (around 9) and I'm worried about his weight. What's a good protein-to-fat ratio I should be looking for to keep him healthy but not too heavy?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For your Lab, you'll want to look for a kibble that has a good balance, but don't get too hung up on the exact numbers, as the best food is often the one that keeps your Lab happy and his energy levels up. A protein-to-fat ratio in the range of 25% to 35% protein is usually a solid starting point for a mature dog like yours. Always check the label, though, because some kibbles are more focused on just hitting a high protein number, and that's just as important as the fat content.",
      "source": "target",
